description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced and highly motivated paediatric physiotherapist to develop their clinical and leadership skills within a friendly, supportive and evolving Community Paediatric Physiotherapy team based in Telford &amp; Wrekin and Shropshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be the Clinical Lead for the Long Term Conditions provision within the Team. This will include managing the Physiotherapy input into the Special Schools in Shropshire, Telford and Wrekin. You will lead on the Special Educational Needs and Disabilities (SEND) for the team.  You will have specialist knowledge and experience in the clinical management of children and young people with long term conditions to be able to enhance the service. You will be expected to deliver training and support the development of other staff. You will have line management responsibilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers the chance to manage a mixed caseload of children and young people, but there will be a bias towards Long Term Conditions. You will bring experience of working in partnership with families, carers, other health and educational professionals and partner organisations. The post holder will be required to work in a variety of settings across Telford &amp; Wrekin and Shropshire.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are systems in place that provide good professional support, training, peer review and supervision. The successful applicant will need to be able to meet the travel requirements of the post.&lt;/p&gt;
